profile_positions.description:
As a performance oriented, data driven, and collaborative Product Owner at Rainforest Alliance, I was responsible for the implementation and continuous optimisation of the organizational capability to deliver digitally enabled business services. Part of the global Engagement, Supply Chain team.
These digitally enabled business services could be be for internal use by RA employees and/or external use such as members or certification bodies. External service I led: certification body management. Some of the activities I performed:

- Analysed business processes to optimise their efficiency / value delivery in close partnership with the business owners, enterprise architects and business process modellers as appropriate;
- Translated qualitative and quantitative data into value for users and user stories with clear and well-structured functional requirements and acceptance criteria for IT developments;
- Lead prototyping workshops and worked closely with the UX designer
- Analysed user feedback to design the service with the UX designer and development team
- Created prototype mock-ups, and/or guided design team/ designer in their creation;
- Translated complex IT solutions into digestible concepts for business stakeholders, and complex business process into functional IT designs;
- Discussed technical challenges of IT solution with the Development Team;
- Coordinated the prioritisation of delivery steps, and develop detailed planning in partnership with project managers, business owners and delivery partners;
- Wrote and/or guided creation of acceptance criteria and acceptance tests as part of user stories;
- Determined edge cases and prioritize the edge cases for development; and
- Managed the ongoing backlog of updates.

Analyzing the data from Customer Service logs, in order to identify painpoints and potential improvements to the product;
Categorizing the data and creating reports;
Aligning with the teams that could benefit from the gathered data;

The Booking.com Partner Behavior team focuses on monitoring how partners (hotels, apartments, etc) operate. Based on patterns and identifying anomalies the team interacts with partners to ensure that they understand their obligations under the accommodation agreements. The team focuses on different behaviors that impact the guest experience and Booking.com its overall relationship with the partner. As a part of No-show guest experience project.

- Calling the customers to validate data provided by the partners;
- Categorizing data and producing reports to analyze the feasibility of potential improvements in the process.

- Guiding the students about the content of the module; 
- Editing and formatting the text-book used for the module;
- Helping them clarify issues and questions regarding to the content delivered; 
- Researching about topics related to the module, such as all dimensions involved in how a product can communicate and how it can be perceived.
